Boil a full #kettle{}.

Trim the @Pak Choi{1} and thinly slice widthways. Halve the @Tenderstem® Broccoli{80%g} widthways.

Crush the @Salted Peanuts{25%g} in the unopened sachet using a #rolling pin{}. Zest and quarter the @Lime{1}.

== Noodles ==

Pour the boiled water from your kettle into a #saucepan{} with @salt{1/4%tsp} and bring back to the boil.

When boiling, add the @Egg Noodle Nest{125%g} and broccoli. Cook until tender, ~{4%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #sieve{} and run under cold water to stop them sticking together.

== Soup ==

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of oil in another large saucepan on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the @Thai Style Spice Mix{1%sachet} and @Yellow Thai Style Paste{45%g}. Stir-fry for ~{30%seconds}.

> Add less Thai style spice blend if you'd prefer things milder.

Stir in the @Peanut Butter{30%g} and @Coconut Milk{200%ml}. Mix well until combined.

Mix in the @Sugar{1%tsp} and @Water{200%ml} for the sauce. Bring to the boil, then lower the heat and stir until everything's well combined.

Add the pak choi to your soup.

Stir well and cook until pak choi is tender, ~{2-3%minutes}.

== Assembly ==

Once the pak choi is cooked, add the cooked noodles and broccoli to the soup.

Bring to the boil again, then immediately remove from the heat.

> Add a splash of water if it's a little too thick - you want a soupy consistency!

Stir in the @Soy Sauce{15%ml} and squeeze in some lime juice.

Taste and add more salt, sugar and lime juice if needed.

Share the noodle soup between your #bowls{}.

Sprinkle over the peanuts and lime zest to finish.

Garnish with any remaining lime quarters. Enjoy!